      "side": 1,
      "message": "So can definitely change Texture to Surface. Part of me was trying to decide if it made it clearer that this was return a GrSurfaceProxyView that was definitely texturable.\n\nSo the ref part comes from copying \"similar\" calls on SkImage_Base/Gpu, where we have getSurfaceProxyView (returns a const\u0026) and refSurfaceProxyView (returns by value reffing the proxy). In this case we don\u0027t have the first version on producer so yeah we could drop the ref part.\n\nAs for just using view, I originally was avoiding that since views were new in Ganesh and I wanted to make in clear what the various functions were returning. If we think we\u0027re at a point where just saying view is pretty clear what we\u0027re referring to I\u0027m happy to go that route.",
